The President and First Lady have announced the special guests who will be seated with the First Lady at the President's First Address to a Joint Session of Congress. The guests include Megan Crowley, who was diagnosed with Pompe Disease at 15 months old and is now a sophomore at Notre Dame, Jessica Davis and Susan Oliver, widows of police officers killed by an illegal immigrant, Denisha Merriweather, who overcame difficulties in school and became the first member of her family to graduate from high school and college, Maureen McCarthy Scalia, widow of Justice Antonin Scalia, and Jamiel Shaw, Sr., whose son was tragically shot by an illegal immigrant gang member in 2008.